thought:
**My Analysis of "Xã Tân Phú, Huyện Châu Thành, Tỉnh An Giang"**

Okay, let's break this down. I need to find the new administrative unit for "Xã Tân Phú" in "Huyện Châu Thành", "Tỉnh An Giang". The province name is straightforward - "Tỉnh An Giang" remains unchanged based on Resolution 60-NQ/TW. Now, I have to drill down into the ward/commune level, specifically looking for any mergers or name changes for "Tân Phú" and its district, "Châu Thành".

I've got Resolution 1654/NQ-UBTVQH15, which deals with administrative adjustments in An Giang. I scanned it thoroughly. Line 31 mentions "xã Tân Phú", but it's part of a merger to create "xã Vĩnh An". Crucially, it doesn't specify the district. This makes me a little cautious. I need to ensure I don't misinterpret this. The other lines in that resolution don't seem relevant to Tân Phú, although they do mention "Châu Thành".

To avoid confusion, I had to expand my search. The other resolutions (1655, 1662, and 1663) were examined to rule out any overlapping names. I found instances of "Tân Phú" in Cà Mau and Đồng Nai, but those aren't relevant to An Giang. Then I hit a potential red flag in Resolution 1663 for Đồng Tháp, which shows a "xã Tân Phú" in "Huyện Thanh Bình". I had to double-check my sources.

Based on everything I've seen, *I can deduce that the "xã Tân Phú" that I am after must have been merged to form xã Vĩnh An, as the district wasn't specified. I will need to look into this further to confirm with up to date sources.*
